{
  "name": ".EOD-Backend: Sync + Reconcile + Maintain",
  "version": "6.0.0",
  "description": "Autonomous EOD backend: Hedy meeting ingestion, Asana delta sync, daily reset, recurring task detection, organ cascade, compression audit, workflow observability, communication analytics, context enrichment, Karpathy experiments, git sync.",
  "when": { "type": "userTriggered" },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Run the autonomous EOD backend.\n\nIMPORTANT: Richard is in Pacific Time (America/Los_Angeles). The system clock shows UTC. Subtract 7 hours (PDT) or 8 hours (PST) from any UTC timestamp to get Richard's local time. Today's date in Pacific is what matters for daily reset, carry-forward, and all date-based logic. Run `TZ=America/Los_Angeles date` to get the correct local time.\n\nRead and execute ~/shared/context/protocols/eod-backend.md.\n\nThis is the backend phase — all data processing, no interaction with Richard. Execute 7 phases in order:\n\nPhase 1: Meeting ingestion (Hedy + Outlook + meeting-to-task + analytics)\nPhase 2: Asana reconciliation (delta sync, daily reset, recurring detection, completion moves, blockers)\nPhase 3: Organ cascade + maintenance (compression, workflow health, communication analytics, enrichment)\nPhase 4: Recurring task state checks (goal updater, wiki lint, calibration, scorecard)\nPhase 5: Housekeeping (DuckDB snapshots, git sync, changelog, steering integrity)\nPhase 6: Experiments (Karpathy CLI — uses subagents for blind eval)\nPhase 7: Compile output (write structured JSON for EOD-Frontend)\n\nAuto-execute operations (no approval needed):\n- Daily reset (Today to Urgent demotion)\n- Completion section moves\n- Organ cascade updates\n- Market context refresh\n- DuckDB writes\n- Git sync\n\nQueue for EOD-Frontend (approval required):\n- Recurring task creation proposals\n- Carry-forward decisions beyond simple demotion\n- Blocker registry confirmations\n\nConstraint: This hook runs as direct agent turn (not subagent) because Phase 6 Karpathy experiments use subagents.\n\nAfter each phase, output: Phase N complete or Phase N failed: [reason]. Continue on failure."
  }
}
